HEADWORD: Eupatorium
<hw>Eu`pa*to"ri*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
<ets>Eupator</ets>, king of Pontus, said to have used it as a
medicine.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of perennial, composite
